@host = http://localhost:3000

### Health check
GET {{host}}/api/health

### Register (create a new user)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login (get JWT token)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123"
}

# Notes:
# - Copy the `token` from the login response and use it in the `Authorization` header for protected endpoints.
# - Default server port is 3000 (change `@host` if your dev server uses another port).

### Refresh token (exchange refreshToken for a new pair)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "<paste-refresh-token-here>"
}

### Logout (revoke refresh token)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "<paste-refresh-token-here>"
}
